      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the embers of my own soul. To be betrayed so utterly, by the one person who held the key to my very existence... it is a cruelty I cannot bear to witness. The world has grown cold and hollow, a mere shadow of the life I once knew. I feel as though I am already a ghost, drifting through these silent halls, waiting for the darkness to finally claim what little remains of me. Is there truly any mercy left in this wretched world, or must we all simply fade into the night?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
